AU  - Cornelli, Francesca
AU  - Li, David D.
T1  - Risk Arbitrage in Takeovers
PY  - 2002
Y1  - 2002/04/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/15.3.837
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 15
IS  - 3
SP  - 837
EP  - 868
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - This article studies the role of risk arbitrageurs in takeovers and the source of their advantage. We show how the presence of arbitrageurs affects the value of the target shares, since arbitrageurs are more likely to tender. Therefore an arbitrageur has the informational advantage of knowing he bought shares. In equilibrium, the number of arbitrageurs buying shares and the price they pay are determined endogenously. We also present several empirical implications, including the relationship among trading volume, takeover premium, liquidity of the shares, and the number of risk arbitrageurs investing in one particular deal.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/15.3.837
ER  - 



